shared_text:
Seton Education Partners
April 1 at 12:37 PM ·

What does #LivingHope look like? It looks like Reyes Claudio, mother of 4 and senior director of operations for Brilla Public Charter Schools working til 9 p.m. on a Friday Night equipping more than 650 families in the South Bronx with computers, books, internet and essential supplies amidst the closing of schools this month...and then staying up to feed her 4-week-old baby throughout the night.

Living Hope is Reyes, along with her school-based operations team, serving with a deep sense of JOY. She was where she was meant to be, where she was needed—comforting others during a time of great fear.

Learn more about Reyes’ story of #LivingHope here: https://www.setonpartners.org/news/living-hope/mott-haven/

Nuestro personal se está preparando para la recogida de computadoras mañana para prepararse para el aprendizaje remoto. Asegúrese de ir al campus de su hijo/a de 10 am a 7 pm para recoger un computadora. ¡La distribución del desayuno y el almuerzo todavía está en BCPE de 10 am a 12 pm todos los días!

Brilla Schools will be closed tomorrow, Friday, March 13th, in light of the proximity of the self-confirmed COVID-19 case in a nearby school and the rapidly-evolving nature of the situation.
.
Las Escuelas Brilla estarán cerradas mañana, viernes 13 de marzo, debido a la proximidad del caso COVID-19 auto-confirmado en una escuela cercana y la naturaleza de la situación en rápida evolución.
